 28 /**
 29  * The global functions and configurations
 30  * @namespace
 31  */
 32 var gxe = {
 33 	
 34 	/**
 35 	 * @namespace
 36 	 * Contains functions and properties for gxe library
 37 	 */
 38   cfg: {
 39     pfxGxe: "g",
 40     pfxHtml: "h",
 41     uriGxe: "http://www.esri.com/geoportal/gxe",
 42     uriGxeHtml: "http://www.esri.com/geoportal/gxe/html",
 43   
 44     /**
 45      * Finds a child of an object
 46      * @param {Object} cfgObject cfgObject The object	
 47      * @param {Object} namespace The namespace
 48      * @param {Object} name The name
 49      * @return {Object} child or null
 50      */
 51     findChild: function(cfgObject,namespace,name) {
 52       var children = cfgObject.children;
 53       var nChildren = 0;
 54       if (children != null) nChildren = children.length;
 55       for (var i=0; i<nChildren; i++) {
 56         var child = children[i];
 57         if ((child.namespace == namespace) && (child.name == name)) {
 58           return child;
 59         }
 60       }
 61       return null;
 62     },
 63     
 64     /**
 65      * Finds Gxe child of given object
 66      * @param {Object} cfgObject cfgObject The object
 67      * @param {Object} name the name of child to look for.
 68      * @return {Object} child
 69      */
 70     findGxeChild: function(cfgObject,name) {
 71       return this.findChild(cfgObject,this.uriGxe,name);
 72     },
 73 
 74 	/**
 75 	 * Checks if children matches given namespace.
 76 	 * @param {Object} cfgObject the configuration object
 77 	 * @param {Object} namespace the namespace to match
 78 	 * @param {Object} name the name to match for
 79 	 * @param {Object} callback the callback function
 80 	 */
 81     forEachChild: function(cfgObject,namespace,name,callback) {
 82       var children = cfgObject.children;
 83       var nChildren = 0;
 84       if (children != null) nChildren = children.length;
 85       for (var i=0; i<nChildren; i++) {
 86         var child = children[i];
 87         var bMatch = ((namespace == "*") || (child.namespace == namespace));
 88         if (bMatch) bMatch = ((name == "*") || (child.name == name));
 89         if (bMatch) {
 90           var _ret = callback(child);
 91           if ((typeof(_ret) == "string") && (_ret == "break")) break;
 92         }
 93       }
 94     },
 95 
 96 	/**
 97 	 * Invokes callback function for each attribute in html namespace.
 98 	 * @param {Object} cfgObject the configuration object
 99 	 * @param {Object} callback the callback function name
100 	 */
101     forEachHtmlAttribute: function(cfgObject,callback) {
102       var attributes = cfgObject.attributes;
103       var nAttributes = 0;
104       if (attributes != null) nAttributes = attributes.length;
105       for (var i=0; i<nAttributes; i++) {
106         var attribute = attributes[i];
107         if (attribute.namespace == this.uriGxeHtml) {
108           var _ret = callback(attribute);
109           if ((typeof(_ret) == "string") && (_ret == "break")) break;
110         }
111       }
112     },
113   
114   	/**
115 	 * Gets value of matched attribute
116 	 * @param {Object} cfgObject the configuration object
117 	 * @param {Object} namespace the given namespace to match attribute namespace
118 	 * @param {Object} name the given name to match attribute name
119 	 */ 
120     getAttributeValue: function(cfgObject,namespace,name) {
121       var attributes = cfgObject.attributes;
122       var nAttributes = 0;
123       if (attributes != null) nAttributes = attributes.length;
124       for (var i=0; i<nAttributes; i++) {
125         var attribute = attributes[i];
126         if ((attribute.namespace == namespace) && (attribute.name == name)) {
127           return attribute.value;
128         }
129       }
130       return null;
131     },
132   
133   	/**
134      * Gets value of attribute from gxe namespace
135      * @param {Object} cfgObject the configuration object
136      * @param {Object} name the given name to match attribute name
137      */
138     getGxeAttributeValue: function(cfgObject,name) {
139       return this.getAttributeValue(cfgObject,this.uriGxe,name);
140     },
141 
142 	/**
143 	 * Gets value of attribute from gxe/html namespace
144 	 * @param {Object} cfgObject the configuration object
145 	 * @param {Object} name the given name to match attribute name
146 	 */
147     getGxeHtmlAttributeValue: function(cfgObject,name) {
148       return this.getAttributeValue(cfgObject,this.uriGxeHtml,name);
149     },
150   
151   /**
152    * Gets text for label attribute from gx namespace
153    * @param {Object} cfgObject the configuration object
154    */
155     getLabelText: function(cfgObject) {
156       var sLabel = this.getGxeAttributeValue(cfgObject,"label");
157       if ((sLabel != null) && (sLabel.length > 0)) {
158         return sLabel;
159       } else {
160         return this.getGxeAttributeValue(cfgObject,"targetName");
161       }
162     },
163     
164 	/**
165 	 * Gets value for maxOccurs attribute
166 	 * @param {Object} cfgObject the configuration object
167 	 */
168     getMaxOccurs: function(cfgObject) {
169       return this.getGxeAttributeValue(cfgObject,"maxOccurs");
170     },
171 
172 	/**
173 	 * Gets value for minOccurs attribute
174 	 * @param {Object} cfgObject the configuration object
175 	 */
176     getMinOccurs: function(cfgObject) {
177       return this.getGxeAttributeValue(cfgObject,"minOccurs");
178     },
179 
180 	/**
181 	 * Gets value for targetName attribute
182 	 * @param {Object} cfgObject the configuration object
183 	 */
184     getTargetName: function(cfgObject) {
185       if (cfgObject.targetNameOverride != null) return cfgObject.targetNameOverride;
186       else return this.getGxeAttributeValue(cfgObject,"targetName");
187     },
188 
189 	/**
190 	 * Gets value for targetNS attribute
191 	 * @param {Object} cfgObject the configuration object
192 	 */
193     getTargetNS: function(cfgObject) {
194       if (cfgObject.targetNSOverride != null) return cfgObject.targetNSOverride;
195       var cfgCheck = cfgObject;
196       while ((cfgCheck != undefined) && (cfgCheck != null)) {
197         var ns = this.getGxeAttributeValue(cfgCheck,"targetNS");
198         if (ns != null) return ns;
199         cfgCheck = cfgCheck.parent;
200       }
201     },
202 
203 	/**
204 	 * Initializes gxe editor configuration and context
205 	 * @param {Object} cfgDefinition the configuration definition
206 	 */
207     initialize: function(cfgDefinition) {
208       this._initializeObject(cfgDefinition,null,null,false);
209       var namespaces = new gxe.xml.XmlNamespaces();
210       var cfgRoot = gxe.cfg.findChild(cfgDefinition,this.uriGxe,"rootElement");
211       if (cfgRoot != null) {
212         this._initializeObject(cfgRoot,null,null,false);
213         var cfgNamespaces = this.findChild(cfgRoot,this.uriGxe,"namespaces");
214         if (cfgNamespaces != null) {
215           this._initializeObject(cfgNamespaces,cfgRoot,null,false);
216           gxe.cfg.forEachChild(cfgNamespaces,this.uriGxe,"namespace",dojo.hitch(this,function(cfgNS) {
217             this._initializeObject(cfgNS,cfgNamespaces,null,false);
218             var pfx = this.getGxeAttributeValue(cfgNS,"prefix");
219             var uri = this.getGxeAttributeValue(cfgNS,"uri");
220             namespaces.add(new gxe.xml.XmlNamespace(pfx,uri));
221           }));
222         }
223       }
224       this._initializeObject(cfgDefinition,null,namespaces,true);
225     },
226 
227 	/**
228 	 * Initializes an object from gxeNamespace and given parent
229 	 * @param {Object} cfgObject the configuration object
230 	 * @param {Object} cfgParent the parent configuration object
231 	 * @param {Object} gxeNamespaces the gxe namespace collection
232 	 * @param {Object} bRecurse if true, then recurision performed
233 	 */
234     _initializeObject: function(cfgObject,cfgParent,gxeNamespaces,bRecurse) {
235       cfgObject.parent = cfgParent;
236       var attributes = cfgObject.attributes;
237       var nAttributes = 0;
238       if (attributes != null) nAttributes = attributes.length;
239       for (var i=0; i<nAttributes; i++) {
240         var attribute = attributes[i];
241         attribute.parent = cfgObject;
242         this._initializeObjectNS(attribute);
243       }
244       var children = cfgObject.children;
245       var nChildren = 0;
246       if (children != null) nChildren = children.length;
247       for (var i=0; i<nChildren; i++) {
248         var child = children[i];
249         this._initializeObjectNS(child);
250         if (bRecurse) this._initializeObject(child,cfgObject,gxeNamespaces,true);
251       }
252       this._initializeTargetNS(cfgObject,gxeNamespaces);     
253     },
254 
255 	/**
256      * Initializes object namespace
257      * @param {Object} cfgObject the configuration object
258      */
259     _initializeObjectNS: function(cfgObject) {
260       var namespace = cfgObject.namespace;
261       var name = cfgObject.name;
262       var prefix = null;
263       var localName = name;
264       var nIdx = name.indexOf(":");
265       if (nIdx != -1) {
266         prefix = name.substring(0,nIdx);
267         localName = name.substring(nIdx+1);
268       }
269       if (namespace == null) {
270         if (prefix == this.pfxGxe) {
271           cfgObject.namespace = this.uriGxe;
272           cfgObject.name = localName;
273         } else if (prefix == this.pfxHtml) {
274           cfgObject.namespace = this.uriGxeHtml;
275           cfgObject.name = localName;
276         }
277       }      
278     },
279 
280 	/**
281      * Initializes target namespace
282      * @param {Object} cfgObject the configuration object
283      * @param {Object} gxeNamespaces the gxe namespace collection
284      */
285     _initializeTargetNS: function(cfgObject,gxeNamespaces) {
286       if (gxeNamespaces != null) {
287         var namespace = this.getGxeAttributeValue(cfgObject,"targetNS");
288         var name = this.getGxeAttributeValue(cfgObject,"targetName");
289         if ((name != null) && (name.length > 0)) {
290           var nIdx = name.indexOf(":");
291           if (nIdx != -1) {
292             var prefix = name.substring(0,nIdx);
293             var localName = name.substring(nIdx+1);
294             var uri = gxeNamespaces.getUri(prefix);
295             if (uri == null) {
296             } else if ((namespace != null) && (namespace != uri)) {
297             } else {
298               cfgObject.targetNSOverride = uri;
299               cfgObject.targetNameOverride = localName;
300             }
301           }
302         }
303       }
304     }
305 
306   }
307   
308 };

311 dojo.provide("gxe.Client");
312 dojo.declare("gxe.Client",null,{
313 	
314   /** @lends gxe.Client# */	
315  
316   /**
317   * This javascript class handles communication with server gxe component and REST document management component.
318   * @class Represents a single gxe.Client
319   * @constructs
320   */
321   constructor:function(){},
322 	
323   
324   /**
325    * Display appropriate message alert in case error occurs
326    * @param {Object} error the error object
327    * @param {Object} ioArgs the io arugements
328    */
329   onError: function(error,ioArgs) {  
330     var msg = null;
331     if (ioArgs == null) {
332       msg = error.message;
333     } else {
334       if ((ioArgs.xhr.status >= 200) && (ioArgs.xhr.status < 300)) {
335         msg = error.message;
336       } else {
337         msg = " HTTP: " +ioArgs.xhr.status+", "+ioArgs.args.url;
338       }
339     }
340     if (msg != null) alert(msg);
341   },
342   
343   /**
344    * This method sends AJAX Http request to Server component endpoint /gxe/definition 
345    * to get editor configuration for given metadata profile. 
346    * Once it received response, the response is passed along to callback 
347    * method for further processing.
348    * @param {Object} context the gxe context
349    * @param {Object} sParam a string parameter
350    * @param {Object} sParamValue string parameter value
351    * @param {Object} callback the callback function
352    */
353   queryDefinition: function(context,sParam,sParamValue,callback) {
354     var u = context.contextPath+"/gxe/definition"
355     u += "?"+encodeURIComponent(sParam)+"="+encodeURIComponent(sParamValue)+"&f=json";
356     dojo.xhrGet({
357       handleAs: "json",
358       preventCache: true,
359       url: u,
360       error: dojo.hitch(this,"onError"),
361       load: dojo.hitch(this,function(responseObject,ioArgs) {
362         callback(responseObject,ioArgs);
363       })
364     });
365   },
366   
367   /**
368    * This method sends AJAX Http request to Server component /rest/manage/document endpoint 
369    * to fetch metadata xml for given id. 
370    * The response is passed along to callback method for further processing.
371    * @param {Object} context the gxe context
372    * @param {Object} id the document identifier
373    * @param {Object} callback the callback function
374    */
375   queryDocument: function(context,id,callback) {
376     var u = context.contextPath+"/rest/manage/document?id="+encodeURIComponent(id);
377     dojo.xhrGet({
378       handleAs: "xml",
379       preventCache: true,
380       url: u,
381       error: dojo.hitch(this,"onError"),
382       load: dojo.hitch(this,function(responseObject,ioArgs) {
383         context.openDocumentId = id;
384         callback(responseObject,ioArgs);
385       })
386     });
387   },
388    /**
389    * This method sends AJAX Http request to Server component /rest/manage/document endpoint 
390    * to save metadata xml for given id. 
391    * In case of errors, it processes the error response and displays in metadata editor UI.
392    * @param {Object} context the gxe context
393    * @param {Object} id the document identifier
394    * @param {Object} sXml the metadata xml
395    * @param {Object} asDraft if document to be saved as draft
396    * @param {Object} callback the callback function
397    */
398   saveDocument: function(context,id,sXml,asDraft,callback) {
399     var u = context.contextPath+"/rest/manage/document?publicationMethod=editor&errorsAsJson=jErr";
400     if (id == null) id = context.openDocumentId;
401     if (id == null) id = context.newDocumentId;
402     if ((id != null) && (id.length > 0)) u += "&id="+encodeURIComponent(id);
403     if (asDraft) u += "&asDraft=true";
404    
405     var dialog = new dijit.Dialog({
406       title: context.getI18NString("client.saving.title"),
407       style: "width: 300px; display: none;"
408     });
409     dojo.addClass(dialog.domNode,"tundra");
410     dialog.show();
411     
412     dojo.xhrPut({
413       handleAs: "text",
414       preventCache: true,
415       url: u,
416       putData: sXml,
417       error: dojo.hitch(this,function(errorObject,ioArgs) {
418         dialog.hide();
419         dialog.destroy();
420         this.onError(errorObject,ioArgs);
421       }),
422       load: dojo.hitch(this,function(responseObject,ioArgs) {
423         dialog.hide();
424         dialog.destroy();
425         try {
426           if (responseObject!=null) {
427             jErr = null;
428             eval(responseObject);
429             if (jErr!=null) {
430               if (jErr.errors!=null && jErr.errors.length>0) {
431                 for (var m=0; m<jErr.errors.length; m++) {
432                   context.messageArea.addError(jErr.errors[m]);
433                 }
434               } else {
435                 context.messageArea.addError(jErr.message);
436               }
437               jErr = null;
438             }
439           }
440         } catch (err) {
441           // handle eval error
442         }
443         if (typeof(callback) == "function") callback(responseObject,ioArgs);
444       })
445     });
446   }
447   
448 });

451 dojo.provide("gxe.Context");
452 dojo.declare("gxe.Context",null,{
453 	
454   /** @lends gxe.Context# */	
455  
456   /**
457   * This javascript class provides a context for processing of gxe editor client component.
458   * @class Represents a single gxe.Context
459   * @constructs
460   */
461   constructor:function(){},
462 	
463   contextPath: null,
464   cfgContext: null,
465   cfgDefinition: null,
466   gptMapConfig: null,
467   htmlParentElement: null,
468   newDocumentId: null,
469   openDocumentId: null,
470   xmlDocument: null,
471   idPrefix: "gxeId",
472   messageArea: null,
473   _uniqueId: 0,
474 
475   /**
476    * Function that builds UI for the editor.
477    * @param cfgDefinition the configuration definition
478    * @param htmlParentElement the html parent element
479    * @param domDocument the document DOM
480    */
481   buildUI: function(cfgDefinition,htmlParentElement,domDocument) {
482     this.cfgDefinition = cfgDefinition;
483     this.cfgContext = gxe.cfg.findGxeChild(cfgDefinition,"context");
484     this.htmlParentElement = htmlParentElement;
485 
486     var elMessageArea = dojo.byId("gxeMessageArea");
487     this.messageArea = new gxe.control.MessageArea();
488     this.messageArea.context = this;
489     this.messageArea.build(dojo.byId(elMessageArea),null,null);    
490     
491     this.xmlDocument = new gxe.xml.XmlDocument();
492     var xmlRoot = this.xmlDocument.initializeRoot(this,cfgDefinition);
493     var domProcessor = null;
494     var domRoot = null;
495     if (domDocument != null) {
496       var ndRoot = domDocument.documentElement;
497       var processor = new gxe.xml.DomProcessor();
498       if (processor.isMatching(ndRoot,xmlRoot.cfgObject)) {
499         domProcessor = processor;
500         domRoot = ndRoot;
501       } else {
502         throw new Error("The XML root element does not match the editor definition.");
503       }
504     }
505 
506     var ctl = this.makeXhtmlControl(xmlRoot.cfgObject,null,true);
507     ctl.xmlParentElement = null;
508     ctl.xmlNode = xmlRoot;
509     ctl.build(htmlParentElement,domProcessor,domRoot);
510   },
511   
512   /**
513    * Function to generate unique identifier for ui elements in editor
514    */
515   generateUniqueId: function() {
516     this._uniqueId++;
517     return this.idPrefix+this._uniqueId;
518   },
519   
520   /**
521    * Gets internationalized string from gxe configuration context for given key
522    * @param {Object} sKey the key to retrieve the i18n string
523    */
524   getI18NString: function(sKey) {
525     var sValue = sKey;
526     if (this.cfgContext != null) {
527       gxe.cfg.forEachChild(this.cfgContext,gxe.cfg.uriGxe,"i18n",dojo.hitch(this,function(cfgChild) {
528         var sk = gxe.cfg.getGxeAttributeValue(cfgChild,"key");
529         if (sk == sKey) {
530           sValue = cfgChild.value;
531           return "break";
532         }
533       }));
534     }
535     return sValue;
536   },
537 
538   /**
539    * Makes Gxe html control based on the jsClass attribute
540    * @param {Object} cfgObject the configuration object
541    * @param {Object} ctlParent the parent control
542    * @param {Object} bInitialize, true if control needs to be initialzed
543    */
544   makeXhtmlControl: function(cfgObject,ctlParent,bInitialize) {
545     var ctl = null;
546     var sJsClass = gxe.cfg.getGxeAttributeValue(cfgObject,"jsClass");
547     if ((sJsClass != null) && (sJsClass.length > 0)) {
548       ctl = eval("new "+sJsClass+"()");
549     } else {
550       ctl = new gxe.control.Control();
551     }
552     ctl.parentControl = ctlParent;
553     if (bInitialize) {
554       ctl.initialize(this,cfgObject);
555     }
556     return ctl;
557   }
558

609     this._array.splice(nIndex,0,obj);
610   },
611

614    * @param {Object} obj the item to be added

626   },

630    * @param {Object} nFromIndex the from item index 
631    * @param {Object} nToIndex the to item index

634     var a = this._array[nFromIndex];

682 
683   /**

693 
694 dojo.provide("gxe.html.HtmlAttributes");
695 dojo.declare("gxe.html.HtmlAttributes",gxe.util.ArrayList,{
696 	
697  /** @lends gxe.html.HtmlAttributes# */
698 
699   /**
700   * @class Util class to perform operations on attributes in gxe html namespace
701   * @extends gxe.util.ArrayList
702   * @constructs
703   */ 
704   constructor:function(){},
705 
706   /**
707    * Applies keywords configuration values to html element
708    * @param {Object} elHtml the html element
709    */
710   apply: function(elHtml) {
711     var n = this.getLength();
712     for (var i=0; i<n; i++) {
713       var attr = this.getItem(i);
714       if (attr != null) {
715         if ((attr.name != null) && (attr.value != null)) {
716           var value = attr.value;
717           if (typeof(value) =="string") {
718             if (value.indexOf("$fire.") == 0) value = null;
719           }
720           if (value != null) {
721             var s = attr.name.toLowerCase();
722             if (s != "tag") {
723               elHtml.setAttribute(attr.name,value);
724               if (dojo.isIE <= 8) {
725                 if (attr.name == "class") {
726                   elHtml.className = value; 
727                   //

741    * @param {Object} name the name of attribute to look for

743    */

746       name = dojo.trim(name);
747       if (name.length > 0) {
748         var lc = name.toLowerCase();
749         var n = this.getLength();

751           var attr = this.getItem(i);
752           if (attr != null) {
753             if ((attr.name != null) && (attr.name.toLowerCase() == lc)) {
754               return attr;
755             } 
756           }
757         }
758       }
759     }
760     return null;
761   },

775         } else {

778           attr.value = value;
779           this.add(attr);
780         }
781       }

945   /**

950   getNodeText: function(domNode) {
951     var s;

961             return s;

964       }

966     } else {
967       s = domNode.nodeValue;
968       if (s != null) s = dojo.trim(s);

974   /**
975    * Checks if document node has children or attributes
976    * @param {Object} domNode the document node
977    * @returns (true) if hode has children or attributes
978    */
979   hasChildrenOrAttributes: function(domNode) {
980     if (domNode != null) {
981       var attributes = domNode.attributes;
982       if ((attributes != null) && (attributes.length > 0)) return true;
983       var children = domNode.childNodes;
984       if ((children != null) && (children.length > 0)) {
985         var n = children.length;
986         for (var i=0; i<n; i++) {

989           } else if (children[i].nodeType == this.nodeTypes.TEXT_NODE) {

992           }

998   /**
999    * Check if node matches configuration object with namespace and localname taken into account
1000    * @param {Object} domNode the document node
1001    * @param {Object} cfgObject the configuration object
1002    * @returns {true} if match found
1003    */
1004   isMatching: function(domNode,cfgObject) {
1005     var targetNS = gxe.cfg.getTargetNS(cfgObject);
1006     if ((targetNS != null) && (targetNS.length == 0)) targetNS = null;
1007     
1008     if (dojo.isIE <= 8) {
1009       if (targetNS == null) targetNS = "";
1010     } 
1011     
1012     if (domNode.namespaceURI == targetNS) {
1013       var targetName = gxe.cfg.getTargetName(cfgObject);
1014       var nodeName = domNode.nodeName;
1015       var prefix = null;
1016       var localName = nodeName;
1017       var nIdx = nodeName.indexOf(":");
1018       if (nIdx != -1) {
1019         prefix = nodeName.substring(0,nIdx);
1020         localName = nodeName.substring(nIdx+1);
1021       }
1022       if (localName == targetName) return true;
1023     }
1024     return false;
1025   },

1027  /**
1028   * Function to match top level element in dom with given namespaces, match xpath , mode and value
1029   * NOTE: matchTopElement does not support full XPath expressions
1030   * @param {Object} xmlNamespaces the namespaces
1031   * @param {Object} domNode the document node
1032   * @param {Object} sMatchPath the relative xpath expression
1033   * @param {Object} sMatchTextNodeValue the match text
1034   * @param {Object} bMust the mode of match
1035   * @returns {Object} matched top level element
1036   */
1037   matchTopElement: function(xmlNamespaces,domNode,sMatchPath,sMatchTextNodeValue,bMust) {
1038     var tokens = sMatchPath.split("/");
1039     var nTokens = tokens.length;
1040     var domFinalMatches = new Array();
1041     var domCurrentNodes = new Array();
1042     domCurrentNodes.push(domNode);
1043     for (var i=0; i<nTokens; i++) {
1044       var bIsLast = (i == (nTokens - 1));
1045       var uri = null;
1046       var pfxPlusLocal = this.splitQualifiedName(tokens[i]);
1047       var localName = pfxPlusLocal.localName;
1048       if (pfxPlusLocal.prefix != null) {
1049         uri = xmlNamespaces.getUri(pfxPlusLocal.prefix);
1050       }
1051 
1052       var domCurrentMatches = new Array();
1053       for (var j=0; j<domCurrentNodes.length; j++) {
1054         this.forEachMatchingElementNode(domCurrentNodes[j],uri,localName,
1055           dojo.hitch(this,function(domChildNode) {
1056             if (bIsLast) {
1057               if (sMatchTextNodeValue == null) {
1058                 domCurrentMatches.push(domChildNode);
1059               } else {
1060                 var s = this.getNodeText(domChildNode);
1061                 if (s == sMatchTextNodeValue) {
1062                   domCurrentMatches.push(domChildNode);
1063                 }
1064               }
1065             } else {
1066               domCurrentMatches.push(domChildNode);
1067             }
1068           }
1069         ));
1070       }
1071       domCurrentNodes = domCurrentMatches;
1072       if (domCurrentNodes.length == 0) break;
1073       if (bIsLast) domFinalMatches = domCurrentNodes;
1074     }
1075     
1076     if (bMust) return (domFinalMatches.length > 0);
1077     else return (domFinalMatches.length == 0);
1078   },
1079   
1080   /**
1081    * Splits fully qualified names into prefix and localName
1082    * @param {Object} sQualifiedName
1083    */
1084   splitQualifiedName: function(sQualifiedName) {
1085     var prefixPlusLocalName = {"prefix": null, "localName": sQualifiedName};
1086     var tokens = sQualifiedName.split(":");
1087     if (tokens.length == 2) {
1088       prefixPlusLocalName.prefix = tokens[0];
1089       prefixPlusLocalName.localName = tokens[1];
1090     }
1091     return prefixPlusLocalName;
1092   }

1136   /**
1137    * Performs escaping special characters in xml.
1138    * @param {Object} s the element or attribute to escape
1139    * @param {Object} bEscapeApostrophe escapes apostrophe if true.
1140    * @returns escaped string
1141    */
1142   _execEscape: function(s,bEscapeApostrophe) {
1143     if (s == null) {
1144       return null;
1145     } else if (s.length == 0) {
1146       return s;
1147     } else {
1148       var sApos = "'";
1149       if (!bEscapeApostrophe) sApos = "'";
1150       var sb = "";
1151       for (var i=0; i<s.length; i++) {
1152         var c = s.charAt(i);
1153         if      (c == "&")  sb += "&";
1154         else if (c == "<")  sb += "<";
1155         else if (c == '>')  sb += ">";
1156         else if (c == '\'') sb += sApos;
1157         else if (c == '"')  sb += """;
1158         else                sb += c;
1159       }
1160       return sb;
1161     }
1162   },

1438   /**
1439    * Function to figure out minOccurs attribute for the node
1440    * returns {Object} the minimum occurance value
1441    */
1442   resolveMinOccurs: function() {
1443     var nMinOccurs = null;
1444     var sMinOccurs = gxe.cfg.getGxeAttributeValue(this.cfgObject,"minOccurs");
1445     if (sMinOccurs != null) {
1446       var pe = this.parentElement;
1447       if ((sMinOccurs == "$parent") && (pe != null)) {
1448         sMinOccurs = gxe.cfg.getGxeAttributeValue(pe.cfgObject,"minOccurs");
1449         if (sMinOccurs == "$parent") {
1450           pe = pe.parentElement;
1451           if (pe != null) {
1452             sMinOccurs = gxe.cfg.getGxeAttributeValue(pe.cfgObject,"minOccurs");
1453           }
1454         }
1455       }
1456       var n = parseInt(sMinOccurs);
1457       if (!isNaN(n)) {
1458         nMinOccurs = n;
1459         if (nMinOccurs < 0) nMinOccurs = 0;
1460         if ((nMinOccurs > 1) && this.isAttribute()) nMinOccurs = 1;
1461       }
1462     }
1463     if (nMinOccurs == null) {
1464       var sUse = gxe.cfg.getGxeAttributeValue(this.cfgObject,"use");
1465       if (sUse == "optional") nMinOccurs = 0;
1466       else if (sUse == "required") nMinOccurs = 1;
1467     }
1468     if (nMinOccurs == null) {
1469       if (this.isAttribute()) nMinOccurs = 0;
1470       else nMinOccurs = 1;
1471     }
1472     return nMinOccurs;
1473   },

1488   /**
1489    * Validates value for various types of input control, checks for acceptable alternate values
1490    * looks up the type of input control from valueType attribute from configuration object
1491    * @param {Object} inputControl the input control whose value is to be validated
1492    * @param {Object}  value the input value
1493    * @returns {Object} status the validation status
1494    */
1495   validateInputValue: function(inputControl,value) {
1496     var regexp;
1497     var status = {"isValid": true, "message": "?ok"};
1498     
1499     var sLabel = inputControl.findParentLabelText(this);
1500     status.message = this.formatValidationMessage(inputControl,"validate.ok");
1501 
1502     // check for empty input
1503     if ((value == null) || (dojo.trim(value).length == 0)) {
1504       var nMinOccurs = this.resolveMinOccurs();   
1505       if ((nMinOccurs >= 1) && !this.getSerializeIfEmpty()) {
1506         status.isValid = false;
1507         status.message = this.formatValidationMessage(inputControl,"validate.empty");
1508         return status;
1509       } else {
1510         return status;
1511       }
1512     }
1513     
1514     // check for acceptable alternate values
1515     if (!status.isValid) return status;
1516     var sAlternates = gxe.cfg.getGxeAttributeValue(this.cfgObject,"alternateValues");
1517     if (sAlternates != null) {
1518       var aAlternates = sAlternates.split(",");
1519       for (var i=0;i<aAlternates.length;i++) {
1520         var sAlternate = dojo.trim(aAlternates[i]);
1521         if ((sAlternate.length > 0) && (sAlternate == value)) return status;
1522       }
1523     }
1524     
1525     // check types, TODO not all xs: types are implemented
1526     if (!status.isValid) return status;
1527     var sType = gxe.cfg.getGxeAttributeValue(this.cfgObject,"valueType");
1528     if (sType != null) sType = dojo.trim(sType);
1529    
1530     if ((sType == "integer") || (sType == "xs:integer") || (sType == "xsd:integer")) {
1531       // the expression is not definitive
1532       //regexp = /^[-]?[0-9]+$/;
1533       regexp  = /(^-?\d\d*$)/;
1534       if (!regexp.test(value)) {
1535         status.isValid = false;
1536         status.message = this.formatValidationMessage(inputControl,"validate.integer");
1537       }
1538       
1539     } else if ((sType == "decimal") || (sType == "xs:decimal") || (sType == "xsd:decimal") ||
1540                (sType == "double") || (sType == "xs:double") || (sType == "xsd:double") ||
1541                (sType == "float") || (sType == "xs:float") || (sType == "xsd:float") ||
1542                (sType == "number")) {
1543       // same expression for any non-integer type, should be more explicit
1544       // the expression is not definitive
1545       regexp = /(^-?\d\d*\.\d*$)|(^-?\d\d*$)|(^-?\.\d\d*$)/;
1546       if (!regexp.test(value)) {
1547         status.isValid = false;
1548         status.message = this.formatValidationMessage(inputControl,"validate.number");
1549       }
1550       
1551     } else if ((sType == "date") || (sType == "xs:date") || (sType == "xsd:date")) {
1552 
1553         // allows yyyy-mm-ddZ or yyyy-mm-dd or yyyy-mm or yyyy
1554         var bOk = false;
1555         var regexp1 = /^(\d{4})$/;
1556         var regexp2 = /^(\d{2})$/;
1557         var parts = value.split("-");
1558               
1559         if (regexp1.test(parts[0])) {
1560           if (parts.length > 1) {
1561             if (regexp2.test(parts[1])) {
1562               if (parts.length > 2) {
1563                 if (parts.length == 3) {
1564                   if (parts[2].charAt(parts[2].length-1) == 'Z') {
1565                     parts[2] = parts[2].substring(0,parts[2].length-1);
1566                   }
1567                   if (regexp2.test(parts[2])) bOk = true;
1568                 }
1569               } else bOk = true;
1570             }
1571           } else bOk = true;
1572         }
1573 
1574         if (!bOk) {
1575           status.isValid = false;
1576           status.message = this.formatValidationMessage(inputControl,"validate.date");
1577         }
1578         
1579       } else if ((sType == "dateTime") || (sType == "xs:dateTime") || (sType == "xsd:dateTime")) {
1580         // TODO not handled
1581         
1582       } else if (sType == "fgdc:date") {
1583 
1584         // allows yyyymmdd or yyyymm or yyyy
1585         var bOk = false;
1586         var regexp1 = /^(\d{4})$/;
1587         var regexp2 = /^(\d{2})$/;
1588         var parts = new Array();
1589         if (value.length == 8) {
1590           parts[0] = value.substring(0,4);
1591           parts[1] = value.substring(4,6);
1592           parts[2] = value.substring(6,8);
1593         } else if (value.length == 6) {
1594           parts[0] = value.substring(0,4);
1595           parts[1] = value.substring(4,6);
1596         } else if (value.length == 4) {
1597           parts[0] = value.substring(0,4); 
1598         }
1599         if (parts.length > 0) {
1600           if (regexp1.test(parts[0])) {
1601             if (parts.length > 1) {
1602               if (regexp2.test(parts[1])) {
1603                 if (parts.length > 2) {
1604                   if (parts.length == 3) {
1605                     if (parts[2].charAt(parts[2].length-1) == 'Z') {
1606                       parts[2] = parts[2].substring(0,parts[2].length-1);
1607                     }
1608                     if (regexp2.test(parts[2])) bOk = true;
1609                   }
1610                 } else bOk = true;
1611               }
1612             } else bOk = true;
1613           }
1614         }
1615         if (!bOk) {
1616           status.isValid = false;
1617           status.message = this.formatValidationMessage(inputControl,"validate.date");
1618         }
1619 
1620       } else if (sType == "fgdc:time") {
1621         
1622         // (hours minutes seconds) examples: hh hhmm hhmmss 
1623         // (offset from GMT) examples: hh+hhmm hhmmss-hhmm
1624         // (suffixed with Z for Zulu time) examples: hhZ hhmmZ hhmmssZ
1625         // (decimal seconds are ssssssss)
1626         var regexp1 = /^\d{2}(\d{2}(\d{2,})?)?$/;
1627         var regexp2 = /^\d{2}(\d{2}(\d{2,})?)?[+\-]\d{4}$/;
1628         var regexp3 = /^\d{2}(\d{2}(\d{2,})?)?Z$/;
1629         if (!regexp1.test(value) && !regexp2.test(value) && !regexp3.test(value)) {
1630           status.isValid = false;
1631           status.message = this.formatValidationMessage(inputControl,"validate.other");
1632         }
1633         
1634       }
1635 
1636     // check restrictions, TODO not all xs: restrictions are implemented
1637     if (!status.isValid) return status;
1638     gxe.cfg.forEachChild(this.cfgObject,gxe.cfg.uriGxe,"restriction",dojo.hitch(this,function(cfgRestriction) {
1639       gxe.cfg.forEachChild(cfgRestriction,gxe.cfg.uriGxe,"*",dojo.hitch(this,function(cfgChild) {        
1640 
1641         if (cfgChild.name == "pattern") {
1642           var pattern = gxe.cfg.getGxeAttributeValue(cfgChild,"value");
1643           if (pattern != null) {
1644             try {
1645               // TODO what about ["g"|"i"|"gi"]
1646               // var regExp = new RegExp("PATTERN", ["g"|"i"|"gi"]);
1647               regexp = new RegExp(pattern);
1648               var obj = regexp.exec(value);
1649               if (!regexp.test(value)) {
1650                 status.isValid = false;
1651                 //status.message = "?invalid "+sLabel+" "+pattern;
1652                 status.message = this.formatValidationMessage(inputControl,"validate.other");
1653                 return "break";
1654               }  
1655             } catch (err) {
1656               console.log(err+", "+gxe.cfg.getGxeAttributeValue(this.cfgObject,"targetName")+
1657                   ", the g:"+cfgChild.name+" is incorrectly defined, "+pattern);
1658             }
1659           }
1660         }
1661         
1662         if ((cfgChild.name == "minExclusive") || (cfgChild.name == "minInclusive") || 
1663             (cfgChild.name == "maxExclusive") || (cfgChild.name == "maxInclusive")) {
1664           var nValue = new Number(value);
1665           var sBound = gxe.cfg.getGxeAttributeValue(cfgChild,"value");
1666           if (!isNaN(nValue)) {
1667             var nBound = new Number(sBound);
1668             if ((sBound != null) && !isNaN(nBound)) {
1669               if (cfgChild.name == "minExclusive") {
1670                 if (nValue <= nBound) status.isValid = false;
1671               } else if (cfgChild.name == "minInclusive") {
1672                 if (nValue < nBound) status.isValid = false;
1673               } else if (cfgChild.name == "maxExclusive") {
1674                 if (nValue >= nBound) status.isValid = false;
1675               } else if (cfgChild.name == "maxInclusive") {
1676                 if (nValue > nBound) status.isValid = false;
1677               }
1678               if (!status.isValid) {
1679                status.message = this.formatValidationMessage(inputControl,"validate.other");
1680               }
1681             } else {
1682               console.log(gxe.cfg.getGxeAttributeValue(this.cfgObject,"targetName")+
1683                   ", the g:"+cfgChild.name+" bound is incorrectly defined, "+sBound);
1684             }
1685           } else {
1686             status.isValid = false;
1687             status.message = this.formatValidationMessage(inputControl,"validate.other");
1688           }
1689         }
1690         
1691         if ((cfgChild.name == "length") ||  
1692             (cfgChild.name == "minLength") || (cfgChild.name == "maxLength")) {
1693           var nLength = value.length;
1694           var sBound = gxe.cfg.getGxeAttributeValue(cfgChild,"value");
1695           var nBound = new Number(sBound);
1696           if ((sBound != null) && !isNaN(nBound)) {
1697             if (cfgChild.name == "length") {
1698               if (nLength != nBound) status.isValid = false;
1699             } else if (cfgChild.name == "minLength") {
1700               if (nLength < nBound) status.isValid = false;
1701             } else if (cfgChild.name == "maxLength") {
1702               if (nLength > nBound) status.isValid = false;
1703             }
1704             if (!status.isValid) {
1705              status.message = this.formatValidationMessage(inputControl,"validate.other");
1706             }
1707           } else {
1708             console.log(gxe.cfg.getGxeAttributeValue(this.cfgObject,"targetName")+
1709                 ", the g:"+cfgChild.name+" bound is incorrectly defined, "+sBound);
1710           }
1711         }
1712         
1713       })); 
1714       if (!status.isValid) return "break";
1715     }));
1716 
1717     return status;
1718   },
1719   /**
1720    * Validates multiple input values
1721    * @param {Object} inputControl the input control currently processed

1730         status.isValid = false;

1733         status.isValid = true;
1734       }
1735     } else {
1736       status.isValid = true;

1999           sbElement.append(pfx);
2000         }

2004       }

2857     var b = this._array[nToIndex];

2874         elB = a.htmlElement;

2885       for (var i=0; i<childNodes.length; i++) {
2886         if (childNodes[i].nodeType == 1) {
2887           nIdx++;
2888           if (nIdx == nRefIndex) {
2889             elRef = childNodes[i];
2890             break;
2891           }
2892         }

2911           if (this.htmlElement.childNodes.length == 0) {
2912             this.htmlElement.appendChild(el);

2914             this.htmlElement.replaceChild(el,this.htmlElement.childNodes[0]);
2915           }
2916           break;
2917         }
2918       }
2919       if (this._activeIndex == -1) {
2920         if (this.htmlElement.childNodes.length == 1) {
2921           this.htmlElement.removeChild(this.htmlElement.childNodes[0]);
2922         }
2923       }
2924       if (bForce) {
2925         if (this.displayInline) this.htmlElement.style.display = "inline";
2926         else this.htmlElement.style.display = "block";
2927       }
2928     }
